= Typus

Rails Plugin to create a basic and default admin interface.

== Requirements

    script/plugin install svn://errtheblog.com/svn/plugins/will_paginate

== Example Usage

To create the first user and copy the stylesheets ...

    rake typus:setup

Default user and password are +admin+ and +typus+.

== Setting your own username and password

You can set your _username_ and _password_ overwriting the following settings:

    Typus::Configuration.options[:username] = 'username'
    Typus::Configuration.options[:password] = 'password'

You can place this settings in a initializer at <code>config/initializers/typus.rb</code>.

== Configuration file options

If the configuration file is broken you'll see a +typus.yml+ text on the admin interface.

Configuration file looks like this:

    Post:
      list: title::string created_at::datetime status::boolean
      form: title::string body::text::15 created_at::datetime status::boolean
      search: name::asc
      filters: status::boolean created_at::datetime

=== Typus Lists

    name::string
    created_at::datetime
    categories::collection
    status::boolean
    language::LANGUAGES

where +LANGUAGES+ is defined at <code>config/initializers/defaults.rb</code> as

    LANGUAGES = [["English", "en"], ["Spanish", "es"]]

=== Forms

    attribute::string
    attribute::text::10
    attribute::collection
    status::boolean
    created_at::datetime
    language::selector::LANGUAGES
    tags::multiple

=== External Forms

    categories::collection

=== Filters

    status::boolean
    author::collection
    created_at::datetime

=== Order

    order: attribute1::asc attribute2::desc

=== Searches

    search: attribute1::asc attribute2::desc

=== Want more actions?

    actions: notify_all::index notify::edit

These actions will only be available on the context +index+ and +edit+ of Typus.

=== Module

Used to group models on the main screen.

    Post:
      module: Site
    Category:
      module: Site
    Template:
      module: System
    Download:
      module: System

